The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 Corporation Bank has raised Japanese yen denominated $100 million loan through a one year syndication facility. Calyon, DBS Bank and Lloyds TSB bank arranged the loan. This is the Mangalore-based bank?s second international loan through syndication within six months. The deal was launched with an issue size of $50 million (Japanese yen equivalent) with an option of retaining $50 million oversubscription. The issue was oversubscribed by more than 100 per cent. The Indian bank has done a total business of Rs 45,780 crore in 2004-05, clocking a net profit of Rs 402 crore for the year. 

 Reliance Infocomm has introduced two zero-rental plans, New Joy 299 zr and New Joy 649 zr, besides automatic STD facility immediately on address verification. Subscribers will be provided free intra-circle calls worth the entire monthly rental, making it virtually zero-rental. Intra-circle calls to all Reliance phones will cost 50 paise per minute while those to non-Reliance phones would cost Rs 1.50 per minute under the New Joy 299 zr and Re 1 per minute under New Joy 649 zr. 

 Shree Cement has clocked a 122 per cent growth in net profit at Rs 29.07 crore in 2004-05 against Rs 13.04 crore in 2003-05. Its net sales for the year ended on March 31 was recorded at Rs 582.08 crore, up from Rs 473.23 crore in the previous year. The operating profit improved to Rs 173.93 crore from 132.37 crore. The company has announced a higher dividend of 40 per cent for 2004-05 compared with 30 per cent given in the previous year.

 The tier II bond issue of Oriental Bank of Commerce (OBC) has been assigned the highest safety rating, LAAA, by Icra. The credit rating agency had put the bank under ?watch? list on July 2004 following the announcement of the merger of the beleaguered Global Trust Bank with OBC. ICRA has now reaffirmed the safety rating for the bank. 

 Bharti Tele-Venture has been adjudged Asia?s Best GSM Carrier in the Telecom Asia Awards 2005, held in Bali. While the Indian cellular service provider won top honours in three categories, Bharti?s chairman and group managing director Sunil Bharti Mittal has got the Best Asian Telecom CEO award. Eight GSM carriers from seven different countries around the Asia Pacific region were awarded at the function. 

 Satyam Computer Services has bagged an Oracle e-business suite deal worth $1 million from Jordan?s third largest GSM operator Umniah Mobile Company. The Indian IT consulting and service provider will implement a customer relationship management solution with POS system for the Jordanian company?s customer contact centre.

